  "text": "Prometheus implements web UI authentication through multiple mechanisms: (1) Admin API Access Control: Implemented in web/api/v1/api.go through an enableAdmin boolean field in the API struct. The admin API functions (deleteSeries at line 2026, snapshot at line 2059, and cleanTombstones at line 2093) all check `if !api.enableAdmin` and return an error if admin APIs are disabled. These functions control critical operations like deleting series, creating snapshots, and cleaning tombstones. (2) TLS and BasicAuth Middleware: Rather than implementing these directly, Prometheus delegates to the external exporter-toolkit library (github.com/prometheus/exporter-toolkit v0.15.1). This is integrated through web/web.go's Handler.Run() method (line 722-770), which calls toolkit_web.ServeMultiple() with a FlagConfig containing the webConfig file path. (3) Web Configuration: The --web.config.file flag is defined in cmd/prometheus/main.go (line 401-404) and passed through to the toolkit. The example configuration in documentation/examples/web-config.yml shows how TLS certificates and basic auth user credentials are configured. The actual middleware implementation for BasicAuth validation and TLS client certificate handling is performed by the external exporter-toolkit library, which Prometheus integrates with seamlessly. The Prometheus codebase itself directly implements only the admin API access control through the enableAdmin flag checks."
}

